WARNING!
Be very careful with the key generator. It adds the following file into the C: \ Windows \ Microsoft.NET \ Framework \ v2.0.50727 \ CONFIG:
 "security.config.cch.new"

lol next time please do some research before posting crap like that. Do you have any idea what the "security.config.cch.new" does ? lol i don't think so.

These files are essentially a cache of the CAS (Code Access Security) demands of your application's code. They allow the in-built security system of the CLR to resolve the security demands of your code slightly quicker.

There was a known issue that could arise from this process, "FIX: Error message when you try to run a Web application that was built by using the .NET Framework 2.0: "Overwhelming changes have occurred" however, this applies to .NET Framework 2.0 and may or may not still apply with .NET Framework 3.5 SP1

You should have at least given it a thought why the file was created in the .NET Framework folder.
